-- Argentine Stocks: Rigolleau, Petrobras Argentina, Tenaris
-- B y   C h r i s t i n e   J e n k i n s
-- 2012-02-02T18:38:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-02/argentine-stocks-rigolleau-petrobras-argentina-tenaris.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 3:15 p.m. in  Buenos
Aires .  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index fell 0.7 percent to 2,816.12.  Rigolleau SA (RIGO)   jumped 8.5 percent, the most in a
year, to 35 pesos. The glass manufacturer said it would build an
oven to increase production capacity about 30 percent at its
Rigolleau plant, according to a statement to the Buenos Aires
Stock Exchange.  Oil industry companies declined as crude fell to a six-week
low in New York.  Petrobras Argentina SA (PESA)  (PESA AF), the local
unit of  Brazil ’s state-controlled oil company Petroleo
Brasileiro SA, dropped 1.3 percent to 7.40 pesos.  Tenaris SA (TS)  (TS
AF), the world’s largest producer of steel tubes used in the
 petroleum industry , declined 1.1 percent to 90.70 pesos.  Soc.
Comercial del Plata SA  (COME AF), the holding company with
subsidiaries that produce petroleum products, fell 0.8 percent
to 65 centavos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
